1
00:01:34,145 --> 00:01:37,401
[NARRATOR]
<i>On the day before
the long-awaited Promised Day,</i>

2
00:01:37,401 --> 00:01:39,501
<i>Alphonse Elric
hid in a train yard</i>

3
00:01:39,501 --> 00:01:42,301
<i>outside the Eastern
training grounds.</i>

4
00:01:42,301 --> 00:01:45,101
<i>However, the Homunculi
Gluttony and Pride</i>

5
00:01:45,101 --> 00:01:46,801
<i>surprised him
with an ambush...</i>

6
00:01:46,801 --> 00:01:51,268
<i>Defenseless against their
attack, Alphonse is captured.</i>

7
00:01:58,734 --> 00:02:01,134
[PRIDE]
Alphonse.

8
00:02:05,301 --> 00:02:08,268
It's time to
wake up, Alphonse.

9
00:02:09,468 --> 00:02:10,768
[AL GRUNTS]

10
00:02:10,768 --> 00:02:12,734
[AL]
Who are you?

11
00:02:15,901 --> 00:02:21,601
[PRIDE]
It's too soon for you to die.
We aren't done with you yet.

12
00:02:21,601 --> 00:02:25,534
There's still so much work
we have in store for you.

13
00:02:28,722 --> 00:02:32,422
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

14
00:02:41,822 --> 00:02:44,548
[FAMERS GRUNTING]

15
00:02:44,548 --> 00:02:47,748
[ED]
Excuse me... Is this
place called Kanama?

16
00:02:51,866 --> 00:02:53,266
[FARMER]
Mr. Ho.

17
00:02:53,899 --> 00:02:56,099
You've got some company.

18
00:03:02,532 --> 00:03:04,699
[HOHENHEIM]
Edward... I didn't think--

19
00:03:06,132 --> 00:03:08,099
Ahhh. That felt good.

20
00:03:08,099 --> 00:03:09,666
Ahh... You could've
at least warned me

21
00:03:09,666 --> 00:03:11,199
you were about
to slug me...!

22
00:03:11,199 --> 00:03:12,632
And with your
metal hand, too.

23
00:03:12,632 --> 00:03:13,666
Hmph...

24
00:03:14,799 --> 00:03:16,499
[HOHENHEIM]
I see you've made
a new group of friends.

25
00:03:16,499 --> 00:03:17,566
We're not--

26
00:03:17,566 --> 00:03:19,699
It's more like we're all
in the same sinking ship.

27
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:20,899
That's right...

28
00:03:20,899 --> 00:03:23,199
And I guess you could say
I'm the captain of that ship.

29
00:03:24,332 --> 00:03:26,099
So you're
the one in charge?

30
00:03:26,099 --> 00:03:28,866
Then I'd like to thank you
for looking after my son.

31
00:03:28,866 --> 00:03:32,132
Sure... But you know he
can be a real pain in the ass.

32
00:03:32,132 --> 00:03:33,232
Hey!

33
00:03:34,632 --> 00:03:37,099
That's an interesting tattoo.

34
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:41,399
Yeaahhh... You noticed...

35
00:03:41,399 --> 00:03:45,199
I guess there's no
point in hiding it.

36
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:48,666
But let's make this
honesty thing mutual, pops.

37
00:03:51,132 --> 00:03:54,399
Look, we need to talk.
The Promised Day is tomorrow.

38
00:03:57,132 --> 00:04:00,699
Fair enough...
I'll tell you everything.

39
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:16,132
[ED SHUDDERING]

40
00:04:16,132 --> 00:04:18,799
[HOHENHEIM]
I was worried this might be
more difficult for you to accept

41
00:04:18,799 --> 00:04:20,466
than it was for Alphonse.

42
00:04:20,466 --> 00:04:22,466
Wait, you told
Al about this?

43
00:04:23,132 --> 00:04:26,666
I did... I'm sure he has his
own thoughts on the matter...

44
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:29,132
...but he accepted
it none the less.

45
00:04:32,566 --> 00:04:36,566
If you want to use me to get
your bodies back... you can.

46
00:04:36,566 --> 00:04:37,766
Are you crazy...?!

47
00:04:37,766 --> 00:04:40,232
Maybe you are a living
Philosopher's Stone...

48
00:04:40,232 --> 00:04:42,599
...but I'm not gonna
sacrifice innocent souls...

49
00:04:42,599 --> 00:04:45,666
It's our fault
we lost our bodies!

50
00:04:45,666 --> 00:04:47,366
[HOHENHEIM SIGHS]

51
00:04:47,366 --> 00:04:49,666
I'm proud my son
feels that way.

52
00:04:53,399 --> 00:04:55,832
There will be
a solar eclipse tomorrow.

53
00:04:55,832 --> 00:04:58,366
He plans on harnessing
it for his scheme.

54
00:04:58,366 --> 00:05:01,166
An eclipse...?
So that's his plan?

55
00:05:01,732 --> 00:05:03,732
Listen, Edward...

56
00:05:03,732 --> 00:05:06,199
He has to be
stopped at all costs.

57
00:05:06,199 --> 00:05:07,566
I need you to help me.

58
00:05:07,566 --> 00:05:10,366
Help you...?
Now look here...

59
00:05:10,366 --> 00:05:12,366
I'm gonna stop that
bearded bastard...

60
00:05:12,366 --> 00:05:15,299
but I'm not doing it because
you want me to help you!

61
00:05:15,299 --> 00:05:17,866
Our best chance at beating
this guy is to team up,

62
00:05:17,866 --> 00:05:21,399
and that's the only reason I'm
even talking to you right now!

63
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:24,532
[ED SEETHES WITH ANGER]

64
00:05:28,432 --> 00:05:29,732
That's fine with me.

65
00:05:29,732 --> 00:05:31,766
It doesn't matter
what your reasons are

66
00:05:31,766 --> 00:05:34,799
as long as you'll
still fight alongside me.

67
00:05:40,532 --> 00:05:42,266
[ED]
Granny asked me...

68
00:05:42,266 --> 00:05:44,632
...to give you
Mom's final words.

69
00:05:44,732 --> 00:05:47,232
[ED BREATHES DEEPLY]

70
00:05:48,499 --> 00:05:52,099
"Sorry I couldn't
keep my promise..."

71
00:05:52,099 --> 00:05:54,132
"...but I'm dying first."

72
00:05:59,799 --> 00:06:01,532
So there, I told you!

73
00:06:01,532 --> 00:06:02,666
[ED GASPS]

74
00:06:19,432 --> 00:06:21,166
[HEINKEL]
Y'know, Ed... Don't
ya think you should

75
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:23,566
maybe try to be a little
nicer to your old man?

76
00:06:23,566 --> 00:06:27,766
[DARIUS]
Yeah, really... You could at
least refer to him as "Dad."

77
00:06:27,766 --> 00:06:30,499
It sounds like you've had
a rocky past with him...

78
00:06:30,499 --> 00:06:33,499
but he doesn't strike me as the
type who'd abandon his wife...

79
00:06:33,499 --> 00:06:34,366
Y'know?

80
00:06:34,366 --> 00:06:36,832
The guy must've had
his reasons... So...

81
00:06:36,832 --> 00:06:39,099
Why don't you give him
the chance to explain?

82
00:06:39,099 --> 00:06:40,299
[ED SCREAMS]

83
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:43,332
Shut up...! Did ya ever think
that I've got my reasons?!

84
00:06:43,332 --> 00:06:45,099
Oh, yeah?
Let's hear 'em then.

85
00:06:45,099 --> 00:06:47,532
You're just stubbornly
holding a grudge.

86
00:06:48,899 --> 00:06:52,432
[GREED]
Heh. Such a whirlwind
of emotions...

87
00:06:52,432 --> 00:06:53,532
I can see why...

88
00:06:53,532 --> 00:06:56,799
The guy's a walking, talking
Philosopher's Stone...

89
00:06:56,799 --> 00:07:01,466
And to make it worse... He
also happens to be your father.

90
00:07:01,466 --> 00:07:03,432
[ED]
There's more
to it than that.

91
00:07:05,499 --> 00:07:09,232
It's just... He's not
what I was expecting.

92
00:07:19,466 --> 00:07:20,499
[TRISHA]
Someday...

93
00:07:20,499 --> 00:07:24,232
I'm going to be a wrinkled
old monster myself...

94
00:07:24,232 --> 00:07:26,299
So today... we're going
to take this picture,

95
00:07:26,299 --> 00:07:29,332
and I'll be able to remember
us all together smiling...

96
00:07:29,332 --> 00:07:33,366
No matter what,
we're always a family.

97
00:07:33,366 --> 00:07:37,132
[HOHENHEIM]
Trisha... I'm going away.

98
00:07:37,132 --> 00:07:39,232
Will you wait for me?

99
00:07:40,566 --> 00:07:42,166
[HOHENHEIM GASPS]

100
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:49,166
[TRISHA]
Of course.

101
00:07:52,399 --> 00:07:54,399
I'll be right here.

102
00:07:59,732 --> 00:08:05,132
I'm sorry, Trisha...
I couldn't keep my promise.

103
00:08:05,132 --> 00:08:07,499
You passed away so early.

104
00:08:08,732 --> 00:08:12,399
You knew that I was unable to
grow old and die with you...

105
00:08:12,399 --> 00:08:14,866
...but you always
believed that I'd come back.

106
00:08:14,866 --> 00:08:18,099
I should've been
beside you, my love.

107
00:08:20,832 --> 00:08:24,099
Tomorrow... Trisha.

108
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:29,766
[OLDER WOMAN]
And here you go.

109
00:08:29,766 --> 00:08:30,599
[ED]
Thank you, ma'am.

110
00:08:30,599 --> 00:08:33,199
[GREED]
And what exactly
is that for?

111
00:08:41,332 --> 00:08:42,299
Whoa!

112
00:08:42,299 --> 00:08:44,532
C'mon, what's wrong with
what you're wearing now?

113
00:08:44,532 --> 00:08:46,799
That doesn't seem
flashy to you?

114
00:08:51,432 --> 00:08:52,466
[ED]
There's a pretty good chance

115
00:08:52,466 --> 00:08:55,566
this is gonna be the last
battle we ever fight.

116
00:08:55,566 --> 00:08:57,732
I want to do it in style.

117
00:09:02,466 --> 00:09:03,832
[ED]
Listen, guys...

118
00:09:03,832 --> 00:09:06,466
you don't have to tag
along with me, y'know...

119
00:09:06,466 --> 00:09:08,799
I'm thinking you'd be
better off going your own way

120
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:11,332
before things start
to get too serious.

121
00:09:11,332 --> 00:09:13,799
Hey, hold on... That isn't
your call to make, pal,

122
00:09:13,799 --> 00:09:15,166
I'm the one in charge.

123
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:16,266
I mean, if it's...

124
00:09:16,266 --> 00:09:18,599
...just about trying to
get your old bodies back...

125
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:19,832
That's not it...

126
00:09:19,832 --> 00:09:21,832
These bodies do
have their perks...

127
00:09:21,832 --> 00:09:24,766
To be honest, I don't really
mind staying like this.

128
00:09:24,766 --> 00:09:26,099
[GREED LAUGHS]

129
00:09:26,099 --> 00:09:28,299
Yeah, now that's the spirit!

130
00:09:28,299 --> 00:09:30,299
So why stick with me then?

131
00:09:30,299 --> 00:09:31,299
Well, why wouldn't we...?

132
00:09:31,299 --> 00:09:33,666
It's not like we have
anything better to do.

133
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:36,499
My animal instincts tell me
something good's comin'...

134
00:09:36,499 --> 00:09:38,499
So I'll ride this
thing out with you.

135
00:09:38,499 --> 00:09:39,699
[ED SIGHS]

136
00:09:41,199 --> 00:09:42,832
And what's your
story, Greed...?

137
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:45,632
Are you hoping to settle the
score with the other Homunculi

138
00:09:45,632 --> 00:09:48,099
for what they did
to your friends?

139
00:09:48,099 --> 00:09:51,499
[GREED]
Are you asking me why I've
decided to return to Central?

140
00:09:51,499 --> 00:09:53,266
I'm not telling ya, kid.

141
00:09:53,266 --> 00:09:55,366
[ED STAMMERS]

142
00:09:58,266 --> 00:09:59,366
Hmm...?

143
00:10:00,866 --> 00:10:03,366
Hey, What's the holdup?

144
00:10:03,366 --> 00:10:05,232
[ED GASPS]

145
00:10:05,232 --> 00:10:10,266
[METAL CLANKING]

146
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:16,832
It's Al!

147
00:10:16,832 --> 00:10:20,166
Oh, man, you
freaked me out there!

148
00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:21,599
Feels like I haven't
seen you in years...!

149
00:10:21,599 --> 00:10:23,199
How've you been, Al?

150
00:10:23,199 --> 00:10:25,599
[AL]
I'm glad to see
you're okay, Brother.

151
00:10:25,599 --> 00:10:26,866
Hey, wait...

152
00:10:26,866 --> 00:10:29,432
I thought you were with Major
Miles over in the Eastern area.

153
00:10:29,432 --> 00:10:32,099
Nothing bad happened, right?

154
00:10:32,099 --> 00:10:34,766
That's actually why
I'm here... We need to talk.

155
00:10:34,766 --> 00:10:36,332
Uh, sure.

156
00:10:39,199 --> 00:10:42,266
Hey, uh... Are you sure
you're feeling alright, Al?

157
00:10:44,266 --> 00:10:45,766
[GREED SHUDDERING]

158
00:10:45,766 --> 00:10:46,732
What do you mean?

159
00:10:46,732 --> 00:10:49,366
Well...
You seem a little...

160
00:10:49,366 --> 00:10:51,132
[LING]
Ed!

161
00:10:51,132 --> 00:10:51,666
Ling?

162
00:10:51,666 --> 00:10:53,399
Get away from him!

163
00:10:55,499 --> 00:10:57,666
That's not...

164
00:10:57,666 --> 00:10:59,166
He's a...

165
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:02,266
[METAL CLANKING]

166
00:11:08,566 --> 00:11:10,166
[DARIUS SHOUTS]

167
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:15,432
What...
What the hell was that?!

168
00:11:15,432 --> 00:11:19,732
[PRIDE]
I see that you're working
with them now... Huh, Greed?

169
00:11:26,766 --> 00:11:30,799
How pathetic that you'd share
your consciousness with a human.

170
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:36,099
Your soul couldn't
be any weaker!

171
00:11:36,099 --> 00:11:38,132
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

172
00:11:41,777 --> 00:11:43,777
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

173
00:11:48,915 --> 00:11:50,634
[MILES]
The Fuhrer's remains
haven't turned up yet?

174
00:11:50,634 --> 00:11:52,499
[GRUMMAN]
So far, they've only found

175
00:11:52,499 --> 00:11:55,633
one of his subordinate's
bodies washed up downriver.

176
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:58,566
It would take some kind of
miracle to live through that.

177
00:11:58,566 --> 00:12:01,366
I'd like the cooperation
of the Northern forces...

178
00:12:01,366 --> 00:12:04,099
...but I intend to oversee
the rest of the search.

179
00:12:04,099 --> 00:12:06,199
You're gonna
personally direct it?

180
00:12:06,199 --> 00:12:08,499
I won't be able to
comfortably sleep at night

181
00:12:08,499 --> 00:12:11,633
until I see his corpse
with my own eyes.

182
00:12:11,633 --> 00:12:13,166
And what about
the plan, sir?

183
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:15,499
Aren't you going to
proceed to Central?

184
00:12:15,499 --> 00:12:17,166
I don't seem to
have much choice.

185
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:19,366
I suppose I'll just have
to let Colonel Mustang

186
00:12:19,366 --> 00:12:21,699
have the bigger slice
of Central pie.

187
00:12:23,133 --> 00:12:25,266
[GRUMMAN THINKING]
<i>Bradley's current
administration will still be</i>

188
00:12:25,266 --> 00:12:28,433
<i>properly functioning
at this point in time.</i>

189
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:30,633
<i>If Colonel Mustang
or General Armstrong</i>

190
00:12:30,633 --> 00:12:32,266
<i>try to make their move now,</i>

191
00:12:32,266 --> 00:12:33,433
<i>every soldier in Central</i>

192
00:12:33,433 --> 00:12:36,733
<i>will be ordered to retrieve
their treasonous heads.</i>

193
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:42,033
<i>And once they're captured...
I'll step in to restore order.</i>

194
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:44,466
<i>They'll take the fall
as enemies of the state...</i>

195
00:12:44,466 --> 00:12:45,599
<i>while General Grumman</i>

196
00:12:45,599 --> 00:12:50,166
<i>will heroically come
riding in on a white horse.</i>

197
00:12:50,166 --> 00:12:53,099
<i>I'll let the youngsters
dive headfirst into danger</i>

198
00:12:53,099 --> 00:12:54,633
<i>and do all the dirty work...</i>

199
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:56,633
<i>and then I'll take
my rightful place</i>

200
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:59,666
<i>as leader of this country
without any risk.</i>

201
00:12:59,666 --> 00:13:00,699
[MILES THINKING]
<i>It wouldn't surprise me</i>

202
00:13:00,699 --> 00:13:04,266
<i>if that's what the sly
old fox is plotting.</i>

203
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:09,699
<i>We may have joined forces to
prepare for the Promised Day...</i>

204
00:13:09,699 --> 00:13:13,466
<i>But I'll withhold my
trust until it's passed.</i>

205
00:13:13,466 --> 00:13:18,499
[SOUNDS OF METAL WARPING]

206
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:25,099
That's not...

207
00:13:25,099 --> 00:13:26,699
[GREED]
It's Pride.

208
00:13:26,699 --> 00:13:28,433
You don't mean that--

209
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,666
[GREED]
Yeah...
That's my brother...

210
00:13:30,666 --> 00:13:33,499
My oldest brother,
I guess you'd say.

211
00:13:33,499 --> 00:13:34,366
[ED GASPS]

212
00:13:34,366 --> 00:13:36,533
A Homunculus...?!

213
00:13:38,099 --> 00:13:42,299
[PRIDE]
So, you've made up your mind to
betray us no matter what, Greed.

214
00:13:42,299 --> 00:13:44,566
Which makes you nothing
more than an annoyance

215
00:13:44,566 --> 00:13:46,366
to us at this point.

216
00:13:46,366 --> 00:13:49,633
Damn it... How did you
even know I was here?

217
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,133
[PRIDE LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

218
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:54,499
How dare you disguise
yourself as my brother?!

219
00:13:54,499 --> 00:13:57,066
[PRIDE]
Who said this
was a disguise?

220
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:03,266
[PRIDE]
This is, without a doubt,
your brother's actual body.

221
00:14:07,066 --> 00:14:08,599
You bastard!

222
00:14:09,299 --> 00:14:12,633
[PRIDE]
First things first,
I need to deal with Greed...

223
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:14,399
Now, Fullmetal Alchemist,

224
00:14:14,399 --> 00:14:17,166
if you would be so kind
as to come with me.

225
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:21,299
Heinkel, you guys
should run for cover.

226
00:14:21,299 --> 00:14:23,133
What the...?
You don't waste any time!

227
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:25,299
Our animal instincts are
telling us that we should

228
00:14:25,299 --> 00:14:27,099
stay the hell away
from that thing.

229
00:14:27,099 --> 00:14:28,699
[ED GRUNTS ANGRILY]

230
00:14:28,699 --> 00:14:31,099
It'd probably be
smart for you to run too.

231
00:14:31,099 --> 00:14:32,599
I'll be just fine...

232
00:14:32,599 --> 00:14:34,499
They need me and Al
for their plans

233
00:14:34,499 --> 00:14:36,033
so they aren't
gonna kill us.

234
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:39,033
But that doesn't mean I've
gotta go easy on them...

235
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:41,966
I've got no problem
taking them down!

236
00:14:41,966 --> 00:14:45,199
[PRIDE]
You're right...
I must take you alive.

237
00:14:45,199 --> 00:14:49,533
But if I slice off a few of your
limbs in the process, so be it.

238
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:59,966
I've gotta make sure to keep
him away from the slums.

239
00:15:05,399 --> 00:15:06,199
[EXPLOSION]

240
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:09,466
A barrier's not
gonna work against him!

241
00:15:11,399 --> 00:15:12,999
[GREED THINKING]
<i>That was close.</i>

242
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:16,533
[GREED YELLS IN PAIN]

243
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:20,499
[PRIDE]
Now then... I've captured
your friend, Fullmetal...

244
00:15:20,499 --> 00:15:22,966
Ready to give up?

245
00:15:22,966 --> 00:15:24,133
You're not going to make me

246
00:15:24,133 --> 00:15:27,999
threaten the lives of the
slum dwellers too, are you?

247
00:15:27,999 --> 00:15:31,299
True to form... He always goes
straight for the cheap shot

248
00:15:31,299 --> 00:15:33,266
in order to
get what he wants.

249
00:15:46,633 --> 00:15:47,666
I think it's about time

250
00:15:47,666 --> 00:15:50,666
I start winning some of
these fights for a change.

251
00:16:00,266 --> 00:16:02,133
[SMALL EXPLOSION]

252
00:16:03,166 --> 00:16:04,499
[GREED GASPS]

253
00:16:09,999 --> 00:16:10,633
[FARMER 2]
What happened?

254
00:16:10,633 --> 00:16:11,499
[FARMER 3]
It's a blackout.

255
00:16:11,499 --> 00:16:13,366
[FARMER 4]
Who shut off the lights?!

256
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:22,099
[ED]
I can't see a damn thing...

257
00:16:22,099 --> 00:16:24,466
But then, neither can he...

258
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:27,433
[HEINKEL]
Greed.

259
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:28,633
Is that you, Heinkel?

260
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:31,266
It's me...
What happened to the power?

261
00:16:31,266 --> 00:16:33,666
I don't know...
But it's saving our asses...

262
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:36,533
Pride can't cast any shadows
without a source of light

263
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:39,533
and he's just as blind in this
darkness as the rest of us.

264
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:41,266
So we got
rid of him then?

265
00:16:41,266 --> 00:16:43,299
No... He's just
lying in wait...

266
00:16:43,299 --> 00:16:45,999
He'll be back at it as soon
as the lights are on again--

267
00:16:45,999 --> 00:16:47,333
Ow, Damn it.

268
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,533
[DARIUS]
So what do we do now?

269
00:16:49,533 --> 00:16:50,533
Hey, Heinkel...

270
00:16:50,533 --> 00:16:53,033
Did you notice the shadow
cast by Al's body?

271
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:56,133
Yeah... It's kind of hard to
miss those freaky tentacles.

272
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:57,733
No, not those.

273
00:16:57,733 --> 00:17:01,566
[GREED]
He kept close to the edge of
the shadows from the forest.

274
00:17:01,566 --> 00:17:04,433
His actual body's probably
just beyond those trees.

275
00:17:04,433 --> 00:17:06,099
His body?

276
00:17:06,099 --> 00:17:08,333
So he's not
inside the armor?

277
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:11,733
No... He's got a special
container that he uses

278
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:13,599
when he's
traveling around.

279
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,266
[DARIUS]
What kind of container?

280
00:17:23,366 --> 00:17:26,433
[PRIDE THINKING]
<i>The skies are
completely overcast.</i>

281
00:17:26,433 --> 00:17:29,666
<i>The others won't be able to</i>
see in this darkness either...

282
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:32,933
<i>The slum's lights
will be on soon enough.</i>

283
00:17:33,299 --> 00:17:35,233
[HEINKEL YELLS]

284
00:17:39,766 --> 00:17:41,666
You're not getting away!

285
00:17:41,666 --> 00:17:43,999
[HEINKEL YELLS]

286
00:17:43,999 --> 00:17:46,999
You've got some pretty strong
nerves to attack a small child

287
00:17:46,999 --> 00:17:48,533
without even flinching.

288
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:51,033
It'd be different if you
were an actual child...

289
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:54,133
but I know what you are!

290
00:17:54,133 --> 00:17:55,399
And not only that...

291
00:17:55,399 --> 00:17:58,666
But my animal instincts
are screaming at me!

292
00:17:58,666 --> 00:18:02,299
They're tellin' me to
kill you before you kill me!

293
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:07,666
[DARIUS]
Ed!

294
00:18:07,666 --> 00:18:09,033
Hey, Ed!

295
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:10,333
I'm over here.

296
00:18:11,566 --> 00:18:13,033
Where's your brother?

297
00:18:13,033 --> 00:18:14,466
Same spot as earlier...

298
00:18:14,466 --> 00:18:17,266
His body clanks
whenever he moves.

299
00:18:17,266 --> 00:18:19,666
Alright... Let's get out
of here for the time being.

300
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,699
I'm not gonna leave
Al behind like that.

301
00:18:21,699 --> 00:18:23,533
I know how worried
you've gotta be...

302
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:27,699
but what if we get close to him
and it turns out to be a trap?

303
00:18:27,699 --> 00:18:29,366
We've gotta stick
close to one another

304
00:18:29,366 --> 00:18:31,566
until Heinkel's
done with Pride...

305
00:18:31,566 --> 00:18:34,533
We don't want to accidentally
attack each other.

306
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:37,266
[LOUD THUDS]

307
00:18:37,266 --> 00:18:38,666
[ED]
So those sounds...

308
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:40,666
That's the lion guy
fighting with Pride?

309
00:18:40,666 --> 00:18:41,799
It's always
your best bet

310
00:18:41,799 --> 00:18:45,433
to let the nocturnal animals
handle fighting in the dark.

311
00:18:48,466 --> 00:18:52,366
[GREED THINKING]
<i>Damned Pride... How was he
even capable of finding us?</i>

312
00:18:52,366 --> 00:18:55,366
<i>Did Father give him
some new ability?</i>

313
00:18:55,366 --> 00:18:56,499
[DARIUS GASPS]

314
00:18:57,599 --> 00:18:59,433
[GLUTTONY GROWLING]

315
00:19:00,166 --> 00:19:01,266
Get down! Now!

316
00:19:01,266 --> 00:19:02,299
[GLUTTONY YELLS]

317
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:05,033
[ED, DARIUS, AND GREED
THUD ONTO THE GROUND]

318
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:12,166
[TREE CRASHES
AGAINST THE GROUND]

319
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:18,466
[GLUTTONY]
I smell you Fullmetal
Alchemist... And I smell Greed.

320
00:19:18,466 --> 00:19:20,499
Of course he'd
bring Gluttony!

321
00:19:20,499 --> 00:19:21,766
That fat slob?!

322
00:19:21,766 --> 00:19:25,299
That makes sense. Now I know how
Pride managed to track us down.

323
00:19:25,299 --> 00:19:27,999
He used Gluttony's sense of
smell to follow our scent.

324
00:19:27,999 --> 00:19:29,966
[GLUTTONY SNIFFS]

325
00:19:29,966 --> 00:19:33,233
I also smell someone
I never smelled before...

326
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:35,666
...and they smell tasty!

327
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:37,633
It's all you...
Go for it...

328
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:39,999
Oh, and he's a
Homunculus by the way.

329
00:19:39,999 --> 00:19:43,066
How do you expect me to
fight a monster like that?

330
00:19:43,066 --> 00:19:46,633
He's relying on his sense of
smell to guide him in the dark.

331
00:19:46,633 --> 00:19:50,233
So right now, I'd say you're
evenly matched for a fair fight.

332
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:51,199
My animal instincts

333
00:19:51,199 --> 00:19:54,299
are calling me an idiot
for listening to you.

334
00:19:55,433 --> 00:19:59,733
So I guess I'm an idiot...!
The first strike is mine!

335
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:01,966
[DARIUS GROWLING]

336
00:20:01,966 --> 00:20:03,366
[GLUTTONY YELLS IN PAIN]

337
00:20:03,366 --> 00:20:04,966
[DARIUS AND GLUTTONY
BOTH GRUNTING]

338
00:20:04,966 --> 00:20:06,466
[GLUTTONY SCREAMS]

339
00:20:06,466 --> 00:20:09,433
Now for the final blow!

340
00:20:11,533 --> 00:20:13,399
Why, Mr. Gorilla...?

341
00:20:13,399 --> 00:20:17,366
Weren't we sticking close to
avoid attacking each other?

342
00:20:17,366 --> 00:20:18,399
Sorry.

343
00:20:21,714 --> 00:20:24,316
[GREED THINKING]
<i>So Gluttony's got the upper hand
on all of us in the dark...</i>

344
00:20:24,316 --> 00:20:28,316
<i>And then we've got Pride to deal
with when the lights are on...</i>

345
00:20:28,316 --> 00:20:31,082
<i>There's not much hope for us.</i>

346
00:20:31,082 --> 00:20:32,716
[LING]
Hey, Greed.

347
00:20:32,716 --> 00:20:33,949
What, Ling?

348
00:20:33,949 --> 00:20:37,616
Switch with me... I can detect
the presence of a Homunculus

349
00:20:37,616 --> 00:20:39,616
when I'm the one in control.

350
00:20:39,616 --> 00:20:42,549
I was the one who warned
us about Pride, right...?

351
00:20:42,549 --> 00:20:45,249
I'll be able to maneuver
around through the darkness.

352
00:20:45,249 --> 00:20:46,249
[GREED SIGHS FRUSTRATEDLY]

353
00:20:48,116 --> 00:20:49,616
[GREED]
It's not like
I have a choice!

354
00:20:49,616 --> 00:20:52,382
But don't go tryin'
to run off with this body!

355
00:20:52,382 --> 00:20:55,082
Just drop it... It was
my body to begin with.

356
00:20:55,082 --> 00:20:57,482
Time to eat you!

357
00:20:57,482 --> 00:20:58,516
[LING]
Got ya!

358
00:20:58,516 --> 00:21:00,149
[GLUTTONY CHOKING]

359
00:21:02,582 --> 00:21:03,216
Heh...

360
00:21:03,216 --> 00:21:05,149
[GREED]
Wow, nicely done...

361
00:21:05,149 --> 00:21:07,082
I'm glad that you and
I are on the same team.

362
00:21:07,082 --> 00:21:08,116
Thanks.

363
00:21:08,116 --> 00:21:08,916
Ling?

364
00:21:08,916 --> 00:21:10,216
That's right!

365
00:21:10,216 --> 00:21:13,749
[GLUTTONY]
You're making me mad...!
All I wanna do is eat...!

366
00:21:13,749 --> 00:21:16,782
But you won't let me eat you,
and I'm getting hungrier!

367
00:21:16,782 --> 00:21:18,316
You're being mean!

368
00:21:18,316 --> 00:21:21,616
So I'm just gonna have
to swallow everything!

369
00:21:21,616 --> 00:21:23,249
I sense somethin' bad.

370
00:21:23,249 --> 00:21:24,549
Bad, how bad?

371
00:21:24,549 --> 00:21:26,216
It's coming this way.

372
00:21:26,216 --> 00:21:27,416
What's coming
this way?!

373
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:28,816
[LING]
I've felt this
presence before.

374
00:21:28,816 --> 00:21:31,782
[ED]
Will you freaks tell me what
the hell you're talking about?!

375
00:21:31,782 --> 00:21:35,616
Hello?! Normal guy here!
I can't see in the dark!

376
00:21:35,616 --> 00:21:37,216
[DARIUS GASPS]

377
00:21:37,216 --> 00:21:38,249
What's the-?!

378
00:21:46,116 --> 00:21:47,049
What happened?

379
00:21:47,049 --> 00:21:47,549
[ED YELLS]

380
00:21:47,549 --> 00:21:49,049
Stay down, kid!

381
00:21:51,749 --> 00:21:53,349
Is there something
else out there?

382
00:21:53,349 --> 00:21:54,649
I'm not sure.

383
00:21:54,649 --> 00:21:56,616
But I think it might--

384
00:21:56,616 --> 00:21:57,649
It is...!

385
00:21:58,249 --> 00:22:00,482
[GLUTTONY]
I smell you.

386
00:22:00,482 --> 00:22:01,749
[GLUTTONY SCREAMING]

387
00:22:01,749 --> 00:22:05,216
I know... that smell.

388
00:22:05,216 --> 00:22:09,682
[GLUTTONY SCREAMING]

389
00:22:10,582 --> 00:22:13,249
[GLUTTONY CHOKING]

390
00:22:16,149 --> 00:22:17,282
[ED GASPS]

391
00:22:25,116 --> 00:22:27,149
I'm glad to see you're okay!

392
00:22:27,149 --> 00:22:31,116
I was wondering when
you'd find me... Lan Fan.

393
00:24:04,182 --> 00:24:06,216
[NARRATOR]
<i>If you're terrified
of the realization</i>

394
00:24:06,216 --> 00:24:07,516
<i>that you must know yourself</i>

395
00:24:07,516 --> 00:24:11,349
<i>in order to know your enemy,
you should run while you can.</i>

396
00:24:11,349 --> 00:24:14,382
But if you choose to accept this
knowledge and stand your ground,

397
00:24:14,382 --> 00:24:18,416
<i>your newfound wisdom is sure
to be rewarded with victory.</i>

398
00:24:19,282 --> 00:24:22,482
<i>Next time on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood,</i>

399
00:24:22,482 --> 00:24:25,582
<i>Episode 48:
The Oath in the Tunnel.</i>

400
00:24:26,649 --> 00:24:28,316
<i>Are you willing
to claim victory</i>

401
00:24:28,316 --> 00:24:31,749
<i>from the blood of your
friends, or aren't you?</i>

